<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top" colspan="2"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Company</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Name</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Enter the name of the company. This is a mandatory field.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>VAT number</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Enter the value added tax identification number of the contact, if required. The VAT number needs to be specified if you are sending items to a commercial purchaser in another country within the EU (intra-community delivery) and you want net totals to be calculated for the order.<br>
After having entered the VAT number, go to <a href="/en/order-processing/orders/accounting#400">System » Client » Select client » Locations » Select location » Accounting</a> and select <strong>Net invoice</strong> for the option <strong>VAT number</strong>. This causes invoices to be issued without VAT for contacts who have a VAT number saved in their data record.<br>
<strong><em>Important:</em></strong> The net setting does not go into effect if you saved tax rates for the customer’s country of delivery.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
