</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="210">2.3. Linking the contact to a company</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you have created the contact without linking it to a company, you can link them afterwards as well. In order to avoid confusion with companies having the same name, the town, street and country of the company are also displayed next to the company name.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter at least three characters of the company name, town, street or country. Your plentymarkets system suggests company data records that have already been saved.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking the contact to a company:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the name of the company, town, street or country in the entry field of the <strong>Company</strong> section.<br>
→ Once you have entered three characters, company data records that have already been saved are suggested.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the company data record from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ All company-related data is displayed in the detail view of the contact.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="220">2.4. Creating a company</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Create the company and save data such as the VAT number, payment due date and early payment discount as a percentage value.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a company:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Company</strong> section, click on <strong>Add new company</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-create-contact">Table 1</a> in the <strong>New company</strong> section.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="230">2.5. Editing the company</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can edit company data that has already been saved at any time. Note that the data of the already existing company data record is overwritten.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing the company:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Edit</strong> in the <strong>Company</strong> section.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the changes as desired. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-create-contact">Table 1</a> in the <strong>New company</strong> section.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The data of the edited company is overwritten and the data of the newly created company displayed in the detail view of the contact.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="240">2.6. Deleting the link between company and contact</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can delete the link between the company and the contact in the detail view of the contact. Note that you only delete the link and not the company data itself. The company data is still displayed as a suggestion after you have entered at least three characters of the company name, the town, the street or the country.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting the company:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the entry field in the <strong>Company</strong> section.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the empty option.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The link between the company and the contact is deleted.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="300">2.7. Editing a contact</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Search the contact by means of the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">filter settings</a>. Open the contact by clicking in the line of the contact to edit the contact’s data such as the date of birth, telephone number and email address, for example. You find explanations of the settings and options in <a href="#table-create-contact">Table 1</a> in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#100">Creating a contact</a> chapter. Click on <strong>Delete contact option</strong> to delete the contact options.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing a contact:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the changes as desired. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-create-contact">Table 1</a> in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#100">Creating a contact</a> chapter.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="350">2.8. Converting a guest account into a regular account</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If the contact has placed an order in your online store as a guest, this account type is saved as contact option in the detail view of the contact. Guest accounts have the value 1. Delete the contact option with the value 1 in order to convert the guest account into a regular account.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Converting a guest account into a regular account:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Contact options</strong> area, click in the line of the account type (type:&nbsp;<strong>Account</strong>, subtype:&nbsp;<strong>Guest</strong>, value:&nbsp;<strong>1</strong>) on <strong>Delete contact option</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The account type is changed from <strong>Guest account</strong> to <strong>Regular account</strong> in the history of the contact.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Inform the contact</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Send your customer an email and inform him or her about the change. He or she can then create a password to be able to log into your online store.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="400">2.9. Deleting a contact</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can delete individual contacts. All addresses that are assigned to the contact are deleted if they are not linked to an order.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting a contact:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search the contact by means of the filter settings as described in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#200">Searching for a contact</a> chapter.<br>
→ The contacts that correspond to the search criteria entered are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the line of the contact.<br>
→ The detail view of the contact opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete contact</strong> in the context menu or click on <strong>Delete</strong> above the detail view.<br>
→ A window opens and you need to confirm your decision.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete</strong>.<br>
→ The contact is deleted and removed from the overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="500">3. Displaying the history</h2>
