<h2 id="1890">14. Managing bank data</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the following sub-chapters, you learn how to add new bank data for your contact as well as edit and delete existing bank data.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1900">14.1. Adding bank data</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Bank data</strong> view, you can add the bank data of your contact. You can add as many data records as you like.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>After saving, the bank data are displayed as cards. Beside the name of the holder and the IBAN, a tag is displayed that shows whether the SEPA direct debit mandate is activated for the contact. If the BIC is saved in the bank data, this is also shown on the card.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Adding bank data:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Contacts</strong>.</p>
</li>
